Oct 22 2009 	I love downtown Vegas and the Golden Nugget!	This was my 4th trip to Vegas. I've stayed at the Aladdin (now PH), the Palazzo, and the Monte Carlo. I've visited downtown before, but never stayed there. This time, I thought I'd give it a try. I'm very glad that we did. We arrived on a Thursday night, around 11pm. Check in was a little slow, but thorough. We were given a booklet of Golden Nugget coupons as well. We used about three of them during our two night stay.Our room on the 14th floor was nicely appointed, two beds &amp; non-smoking - just as I asked for. Everything was very clean. I wished that our room had a mini-fridge and coffee maker, but we were ok without it. The complimentary toiletries were good sized and nice. After getting settled in, we went down to the Grille for a bite. We used a $2 off per person coupon. The food was really good, and it came out fast, considering it was after midnight.The pool area was great, if but a little small - really liked the shark tank. The only real downside was that there wasn't a whole lot of sun reaching the space. It more than likely has a lot to do with the time of year (the sun doesn't get as high- we had similar problems finding chairs in the sun at the Venetian later in the week), but you have to scope it out early if you want to get a spot in the sun.We ate at the Buffet for breakfast (used a two-for-one coupon and got breakfast for $10 for both of us!) and it was pretty tasty. I recommend going earlier than 10am if you want all of the breakfast selections... at around 10:15 they started switching over to lunch.All in all, I would definitely return to the Golden Nugget. It's a good value and a fun, laid back atmosphere. I'm hoping to give the spa a try during my next stay.*I also signed up for their 24 Karat Club (a must if you like Vegas and getting offered room specials!)	
