Sep 12 2009 	Brill Time	Stayed here in March 09, it was a very good hotel and i would definatly stay there again.Hotel- Excellent check in was quick and precise and directed to our rooms straight away all the requests we made were given to us. Room was really big with a very spacious bed and the bathroom was large too. Room very clean and cleaned every day. the cleaners were also very nice and friendly. Tv was massive bigger than my one at home and view of the strip was good as well.Pool- The pool was of a good size and plenty of sunbeds for the time of year, i could imagine it being a little cramped in high season though. the shark enclosure was amazing as was the slide going through it. The bar has plenty to choose from and the waitresses were always there to help. One minor complaint is that every time i went to the bar i got asked for id which can get a bit tired but thats the way they work over there.Casino- had plenty of slots and things to do in it and we had a really good time there.Freemont Street- Excellently located right in the middle of the experience and it felt like a party every night down the street. was great for cheaper slots and tables and drinks a lot better priced.The Strip - was amazing although the hotel is definatly not close to it so dont get the impression that you can walk to it. Definatly get the bus that runs every ten mins it runs directly by the hotel and only costs $7 a day ticket. Plenty to do on the strip even just going round all the hotels can take a full day up.Excursions/shows - Get your show tickets and excursion tickets from half price tickets they have shops up and down the strip and the tickets are half the price of booking them at home or through your agent.All in all a brill hotel and so much cheaper to stay at the freemont end of town knocked £100 per person off the strip priced hotels and got the same experience just by getting a bus	
Sep 10 2009 	Great place for a great price	We stayed at the Golden Nugget for 3 nights during the &quot;Summer of '69&quot; festival. Check in line was long, but was expected on Labor Day weekend. Did not get into room until 5pm due to our carpet being cleaned. No problem, we ate lunch and hung out at the pool. Our room was clean and well decorated, but carpet still damp. Slight smell of smoke, even though it was a non-smoking room. Upon returning late that evening, we found out why the carpet was &quot;cleaned&quot;. The air conditioning unit was leaking water and carpet was wet from the unit to the bed. Went to front desk early the next morning and they were more than happy to move us to another King room, 19th non-smoking floor. Much better. The pool was fantastic. Water slide, 2 waterfalls, shark tank, black-jack tables, and pool side bar with food (sandwiches, appetizers, etc.) This was also a nice place to end your evening with a cold beverage and good company. Staff was always friendly, rooms were cleaned early each day, and by far this is the cleanest hotel and casino on Fremont Street. Plan to stay here again soon.	
