Aug 30 2009 	Gold Club rooms not worth the money pool area is way too crowded.	Stayed there five nights, just got home two days ago. The Gold Club rooms are not worth the money. Small, dark, even the bedside lamps not good for reading. They have a cover over the air conditioner, like a small coffe table type of thing, with louvers for the air to pass thru. Had to remove it each day so the room would get cooler. Soon as we pulled it out I could feel the cool air flowing throughout the room. The bathtub/shower combo sucks. You have to get in tub then turn everything on. The rain shower head was a pain, my wife had to turn on tub faucet then lie down in order to rinse her hair out, rain head would take forever. At least three of the five mornings we were awakened by emergency vehicles sirens from the streets below, and we were on the 17th floor, room 1710. The swimming pool is way too crowded with no room to spread out. Surrounding properties have gone way downhill last five or so years. I will not be staying downtown again, used to enoy staying there. I want to mention to everyone that they should boycott the 6 to 5 blackjack games. Most of the Vegas properties have made the game unplayable, used to never see 8 deck shoes there, no doubling down after split pairs on single deck. Terrible blackjack games. If enough people stop playing these highly unfavorable bj games they will revert back to the old rules. The South Point has double deck, 3 to 2 on bj, dbl after splits, $5 minimum. Look around and find the better games, don't let the casinos get away with changing the rules so they can take your money faster. Hope this review helps, plz e-mail if u have any questions regarding your Vegas trip. I visit there 3 to 4 times yearly, play poker, Blackjack, some slots (only when bored, lol).	
Aug 29 2009 	Great hotel in Classic Las Vegas style!	Just got back from Vegas and I was happy to have picked this hotel. The room was clean and comfortable, with no discernable noise at night from the street or neighbors- the soundproofing must be of good quality. I was in the south tower, as I had requested a nonsmoking room. It was a bit of a hike to the room (as it is farthest away from Fremont street) but I didnt mind as I am in good shape. People who are not may find it a pain. I would typically out to do an activity in the morning when it was somewhat cooler and be back at the hotel in the early afternoon to relax and have a nap before going out in the evening, so , I really apperciated the soundproofing! The pool area is great, and I didnt have a problem getting a chair. The hot tub area is open late, and it was great to relax with a cigar and drink at the end of the day here. The Duece bus would leave every 15 mins or so from the south end of Fremont st. and take you anywhere you wanted to go on the strip. The $15 three day unlimited pass is the best value- as it also is good for any other bus in the city. There are connections to go to the outlet malls, convention centrers, etc. The bus drivers were friendly and helpful about answering questions. A tip about shopping- I was planning to go to the outlet mall but found more than enough to buy at one store- The ROSS dress for less on the strip beside the Rivera hotel. Get there in the morning at 930 for the best selection. I am male and not usually a power shopper, but I make an exception here- I bought 5 pairs of shoes, 6 ties, 5 shirts, etc, etc at 10-20% of retail, and all designer brands. Its hard to argue when a Ralph Lauren silk tie is $7.99. the bus stops in front of the Slots a fun and the Ross store is across the street and a little south. I don't gamble so I can't comment on that. What I can recommend is a couple of other things I went to- The atomic testing museum, West on flamingo from the strip, reachable by bus after a transfer. It was well worth the $12 admission, and uncrowded. I also took a bus west of the strip on tropicana to get to The Gun Store- an indoor shooting range and retail store. Here you can get to target shoot almost any gun- from pistols to fully automatic machine guns. I chose the WW2 package ($99.95) and was pleased with the opportunity to try the .45 automatic, the Thompson smg, and the Mp-40. There was a M-16 painted pink for the ladies. Even children can get in on the shootin, supervised by their parents. the staff were very helpful and patient! The Liberace museum was also on the way there, if you would like to take that in as well. There is a lot of good food deals around the fremont street area, and the Tuesday and Friday all you can eat seafood buffet at the Fremont hotel is not to be missed. The Golden Gate hotel has the best shrimp cocktail for $1.99. I agree with what a previous reviewer said about the Fremont area being cleaner and freindlier than the main strip- most folks there are just out to have fun. some of the live bands (nightly) and street artists are very talented. There are also many shops selling every cheesy LV souvenir you can imagine- but most of them also sell cold beer so that makes up for it! I would recommend the Golden Nugget and dont mind answering other questions. Enjoy your holiday here!	
