Aug 27 2009 	Golden Nugget best value in downtown Las Vegas	The Golden Nugget is the best value for your money in downtown Las Vegas because you get a 4 star hotel with a reasonable price. We stayed their for a seminar. They offer a VIP check-in for an additional $20. It is well worth it because you do not have to wait in long check in or check out lines. You just go to the VIP room around the corner from the check in desk. They have some cheese, fruit, crackers, and bags of nuts offered while checking in and out. The rooms are nice. They have a great pool with jaquzzi's, a water slide and a large shark tank with sharks and fish swimming in the middle of the pool. They have many choices of restaurants, a good nite club with a balcony over looking the downtown walkway and have two Starbuck's inside.If you are on a budget walk over to the Plaza hotel where they have Mc Donald's, Subway, and a reasonably priced buffet. A great buffet with lots of variety and good food, desserts, and drinks included is around the corner at the Main Street station casino. The price is resonable for what all you get. If you want to save on a beer or two walk over to the ABC market towards the Plaza casino. At the Gold Spike they have shrimp cocktails for $1.99 or if get a players card there then the shrimp cock tails are 99 cents. I did not eat at the Golden Nugget buffet so I can not comment on it.It was a great stay. I would recommend the Golden Nugget to my friends if they are going to stay downtown. It's especially good if you don't have a car because of it's location and if you want to go to the strip you can take a bus for $3 each way.	
