Jun 16 2009 	Good stay at the Golden Nugget	We spent one night in a South Tower room at the beginning of our trip and one night in a North Tower room at the end (our prime destinations were Brice and Zion National Parks). The North Tower Rooms are somewhat more expensive and considered &quot;premium&quot;.All the basics were fine with both rooms. They were clean, quiet, and the bed was very comfortable. Parking is in a deck across a small side street and is free, as long as you hang on to a little parking slip they will give you on check in.One thing that surprised us was how far &quot;The Strip&quot; is from downtown. All the cross roads are under construction, nobody pays any attention when driving, &quot;strip&quot; parking is crazy, and side streets get sleazy looking really fast. You would need to plan on 45 minutes to an hour to get to MGM, for instance, to go to a show. So it's best to come to this city with a lot of patience.The difference between north and south tower: a few more toiletries, closer to the casino (but farther away from the parking deck), a somewhat better view, bigger tv (but not a lot of channels), larger room. Again, both rooms were fine overall...it depends on your priorities.	
