 bad. I really hate that as i see the potential of this hotel. I used to love that hotel They have a Mcdonalds there. Ask for Senior citizens drink/coffee. Cheaper. Never did find Burger King even though it shows ads on it. The Plaza has a Mcdonalds and a Subway in it. They do not offer the senior discountFor bowlers: Binions has a shuttle bus that takes you to the Cashman Center at no charge except tip.Its in the back of Binions. The taxi cost $6.50 from fremont street to Cashman.Walking distance is about 20 minutes from Main street. Parking at the Cashman was $3.00. Transportation:Fremont has a free Charter bus that takes you to Sam's Town. From there you takeanother free bus ride to the strip(Harrah's &amp; Riviera). Last run back is approx 10:45 p.m. This is how we got around. My husband's brother took the Deuce from Stewart street (downtown) to the strip.Information is on the RTC website. I believe it was $7.50 one way. Also the Cat (local bus) information in on the RTC. I believe that approx $1.50. I called them to find out what bus route to take to the strip. I ended up going out on the fremont bus.website. We ate at the Margaritaville on the strip. We ate a volcano. Large mound of chips/chili &amp; cheese. This could eat 4. We bought one for two. Way to much. This was great.I am glad we stayed at the Golden Nugget. It is so much closer to the bowling center.If the price is right again i would stay there again	
Jun 2 2009 	Golden Nugget LasVegas...What a great hotel!!	We arrived on May 1, 2009 to stay for 5 days while my husband bowled in the USBC tournament. Service was exceptional from start to finish. The guys at the front door of the hotel were friendly &amp; courteous. Check-in was a piece of cake with very knowledgeable and friendly staff. My husband shipped his bowling balls ahead of us for ease of travel and asked the staff to locate the package. Within 5 minutes of us arriving in our room, the box was delivered to us. The room was just as their website described. We had a king-sized bed and a very large, comfortable room. My only complaint (which is certainly not the hotels fault) was that we stayed on a smoking floor (hubby is a smoker). Room had a desk, a table with 2 chairs, dresser with a large flat screen TV on top, dressing table with makeup mirror, large closet with a safe, iron, ironing board, hairdryer and extra pillows. And the best of all...2 absolutely, fabulous bathrobes! We had dinner at the buffet that evening and breakfast there everyday after that. The weekend brunch was just fabulous with your choice of champagne or mimosa's and lots of great choices with everything you could imagine for brunch! Saturday was my day at the spa, while hubby went to play in the casino. I just started working out with a trainer and was sore from being out of shape, so I decided to go for the &quot;sports massage&quot; and facial. I was pampered from the start and the staff was great. I was brought into the spa and shown everything there (which includes the salon, fitness area, hot tub, sauna &amp; dry heat rooms). I was given a pair of sandals and brought to the changing/waiting room. I was given a locker which had a robe to change into and where I could keep my clothes while I was at the spa. The waiting area was comfortable with lounge/chaise chairs and cold refreshments &amp; snacks. I changed and was immediately called in for my massage. The massage was great and lasted for 50 minutes...not so much relaxing as it was healing my sore muscles. I was then brought back to the waiting area to wait to be called in for my facial. It was a 30 minute facial which everyone should experience! Throughout my massage &amp; facial, both staff members were constantly asking if I was comfortable and enjoying my spa experience. Once my facial was done, I decided to go into the hot tub. I enjoyed that to the point where I became wrinkled! Once I was ready to leave, the shower area was complete with everything one could possibly need...shampoo, conditioner, razors, washcloths, towels, etc. The makeup area was complete with combs, hairdryers, deodorant, body lotions, etc. The experience was wonderful, relaxing and something I would certainly recommend to anyone! Later that afternoon, the day continued with a BIG win on the Kentucky Derby which was shown on 4 big screens in the Grand Ballroom. Sunday was bowling day in the afternoon, so most of the morning was spent on the casino floor (which was fun &amp; profitable!) Monday morning (VERY early...6am) was bowling day #2, so we were back at the hotel by 10 am. I wanted to spend some time by the pool while hubby went to play in a poker tournament (which he won!!!) The pool was just AMAZING! Waitstaff was very courteous and busy! Towels were supplied poolside and frozen strawberry margaritas were great. The shark tank was just the coolest thing I have ever seen. To be able to take a dip in the pool and swim up to the fish and sharks was just amazing. Very relaxing lounge chairs in the shallow part of the pool were refreshing too. Wished I had worked in a trip down the slide, but was enjoying myself too much relaxing in a lounge chair. 4 blackjack tables poolside were very good to hubby as well. Casino was very comfortable, clean and well laid out. Service was exceptional; rates very reasonable. Will DEFINATELY stay again next visit!	
Jun 2 2009 	Fabulous Hotel with pleasant 	We had read all the reviews on Tripadvisor regarding this hotel and viewed hotels own website plus others, so expected this hotel to be a decent one.We were not disappointed in the slightest on fact our expectations were exceeded.We arrived late (midnight) and we had a very quick and easy check in. Our room was a King Deluxe in the South Tower. Room was big and was identical to the photos on the website. Room was lovely and clean as too was the bathroom. Only thing lacking in the bathroom was a mini showergel, but this is really being picky as we had everything else and more besides. Bath was low with easy access and hand rail.The cleaners came to tidy our room and make the bed daily, they changed the sheets every other day, and they did a fantastic job.The food at the hotel, buffet and Carson Street Cafe is excellent. We only ate at those places did not try other places. In fact we had a buffet breakfast most days and found that we filled up on it so much so that we really didnt feel the need to eat anything else for the rest of the day, we would have an evening snack of sandwich or similar and we would be fine.The South Tower alone had 16 elevators, 8 for the even floors and 8 for the odd floors. There were elevators and moving stairways upto the buffet restaurant and Showroom. The casino floor was all on groundfloor level as was the Tank, other restaurants etc.The casino was nice and airy, not too much smoke and did not smell as some other casinos did.The staff at the hotel did everything they could to assist us, even the bell hops, one of which booked and arranged a trip for us to hoover dam at short notice.The Deuce bus stop to the strip is just a couple of blocks away, and we used this service everyday. Costs $3 for one way trip $7 dollars for all day or $15 dollars for 3 days. The 3 day pass proved really good value. Journey sometimes was quick but other times could be lengthy but we felt this just depended on time of day and driver.However most nights we would return from visitng the sights on the strip to the hotel and Fremont Street as the party atmosphere there was great fun and more enjoyable than the strip.When you look at the Hotels website and wonder if it really does look like the photos or have they &quot;glossed&quot; it up a bit - they havent, the hotel really does look like that and is a fantastic place to stay.It can get busy at the weekend however this adds to the party atmosphere.We would stay there again without hesitation.	
