May 3 2009 	Golden Nugget Vegas-Awesome Stay!	Just got back from our awesome stay from the Golden Nugget Las Vegas! So here is my review, hope you find this useful!We booked our package through Allegiant Air, flying out of Eugene, Oregon, three nights, and a round trip shuttle to and from the airport. All that for $600 total. This was definatly the way to go, and here is why...Allegiant Air is a cheap no frills airline, its been the third time i've flown to Vegas with them and its been great everytime. The airline was ontime leaving out of Eugene and we actually landed about 10 minutes early so that is always great when you are excited! So the bad thing about flying into Vegas right now is they only have One Tram working. So there is a long wait to get to baggage claim. This will be ongoing for sometime. Just a warning so be ready for this, also, keep that in mind when you return, give yourself plenty of time to get through security and back on the One Tram thats working.The round trip shuttle option offered through Allegiant was a great deal, saved a few bucks, it was $28 round trip. It only took minutes after we got our bags to be on the way to the hotel so that was pretty awesome I thought. If you outright get a shuttle it can be $14 per person each way, and a cab from the airport to Golden Nugget yikes! We did the regular check in the Golden Nugget, took only minutes and the room we reserved online was ready for us so no need to pay the extra $20 for VIP. So here's the great deal for a prepaid trip to Golden Nugget, they do not need your credit card or debit card for incidentals! Otherwise they hold $100 per night, so that was another good deal!We stayed in the South Tower, 10th floor room 10109 and had a view of the Stratoshper Tower. So all the complaints about the walk from your room to the casino floor, don't worry about it, its not bad at all! I've stayed on the strip, now that's a long walk! They do have those pesky Tahiti Villiage people along the way to the elevators, so just don't make eye contact, keep walking and you'll be ok! Actually its not that bad at all.So the food was great there, we ate at Lillies Noodle house, two of us came to $60 and the food was great! Ate at Carson Cafe for breakfast, great again. Ate at the buffet for breakfast, not the best but only $10 each so what do you want for only ten bucks?? The thing i liked about the buffet was the veiw of the pool! So the staff was excellent, everyone was very friendly! I can't wait to stay here again, i receomend this hotel to anyone wanting a great Vegas experiance. How can you beat it? Catch the Duece to the Strip, its only $3 one way or $7 for an all day pass. We caught a cab from Excallaber to Freemont and it was $25 so cabs are pricey!! Just be warned.Oh, about the room, i didn't think there was a safe in the rooms because it's not listed on thier web sight, but there is one in the closet. Also blow dryer, bathrobes, iron, ironing board, extra pillow, nice!	
