Apr 24 2009 	2nd stay---still impressed (most of the time)!	My husband and I just returned from our 2nd stay at the Golden Nugget. We arrived very early and knew that we would not be able to check in. We had booked a VIP Gold Club Room. Check-in at the VIP Lounge is definitely worth the extra charge. NO LINES! NO WAIT! The 2 staff members there were very friendly and helpful. They took our cell phone number to call us when the room was ready. We inquired about checking out bags so that we could walk around until our room was ready. They were very helpful and directed us to the bell desk. Problem #1 begins. We walked over to the bell desk. The bellman there seemed confused about what were asking. While we tried to explain, he became argumentative and telling us that we should have entered the hotel from a different area. We had no idea what he was talking about and explained that the VIP lounge staff told us to go there. Nevertheless, the conversation continued to go downhill. We finally got our bags checked in and we promptly went back to the VIP lounge to tell them what we experienced. Again, the 2 staff members there were extremely helpful and apologetic. They truly seemed concerned about our experience. A few hours later, we received a call on the cell phone as promised when our room was ready. Because the hotel was booked, we were upgraded to a suite, which was ready earlier. We entered the 2 room Parlor Suite and were not disappointed. One thing I like about the Golden Nugget, is that their rooms are exactly as they are pictured on their website. Our stay was enjoyable and uneventful except for a few issues with housekeeping. Water and glasses in the room were not replenished daily. Only received turndown service 1 of the 4 nights we were there. While this may seem trivial to some, we paid extra for the upgrades to make our trip nicer, so not getting this was disappointing. As usual, room service was wonderful. Arrived within a short period of time. Service is always great! We ate at The Grotto, Vic &amp; Anthony’s, Carson Street Café and The Buffet. All exceeded our expectations except the Buffet. It was extremely crowded and way overpriced for what you got. The food was average at best. We enjoy staying in the downtown area and will always choose the Nugget. We are looking forward to the new rooms in the new tower!	
