Apr 23 2009 	great stay- great location	This was our third trip to Las Vegas and our first stay Downtown. We have previosly stayed at the Flamingo and Treasure Island. We were satisfied with both, but not overly impressed with what you get for their prices. We chose the Golden Nugget because of their reputation for being the nicest hotel Downtown. From what we saw of the other casinos, Golden Nugget is BY FAR the nicest and the classiest. We played at the other casinos, but I couldnt get my husband to eat anywhere else but the Golden Nugget. We chose a deluxe room in the North tower because of the upgrade features. The flat screen TV was very large and the bed was great. The sheets were very comfortable and the pillows and comforter were super soft. We LOVED the room. It was better than the standard room at the Flamingo and on par with the remodeled rooms at Treasure Island.  The common areas are beautiful and the pool was nice. The only complaint about the pool area is the number of available chairs. We were there during a HOT spell, and before the pool even opened, most of the lounge chairs were taken. This is concerning considering we saw a sign in the construction area saying there were 500 more rooms being built. Hopefully they expand the pool area too. As for the construction, we only heard noise one morning and it was barely noticable. Since the construction area overlooks the pool, we did see more than one construction worker staring down at the pool area, presumably checking out the bikinis by the pool.  The casino and restaurants were very nice and had a very classy feel. I dont think the slots were as loose as the other hotels downtown and the table limits are higher. I realized quickly that since the new building needed to be funded , the slots would probably be tighter . Most of my gambling dollars went across the way to Binions and their $2 roulette.  As for location, Downtown is the way to go. We love the Fremont Street experience light show, the entertainment and the action at night. The clientele is a little rough at times, but it is on some parts of the strip too. One good thing, no annoying people flicking their nudey girl cards at you. You can walk easily to multiple different hotels that have good gambling . We have found that the strip casinos take your money FAST. Downtown you can play longer and have a lot more fun. Overall, we had a great time. We will never stay or gamble on the strip again.	
