Jan 20 2009 	Is complimentary coffee not the minimal standard these days?!:)	Spent 4 nights at GN for New Year's Eve. I appreciated the quick and early check in. I arrived and received the room around noon, even though the usual check in time is 3pm. During my stay the service was great from security, to receptionist, room service, and housekeeping etc. The room was very clean, with comfortable pillow top king bed, dark curtains, tv, large nice bathroom, with spa robes, hair dryer, toiletries, iron and ironing board, safe. The heated pool with water slide and fishtank is a nice feature. Still, I cannot give a better rating than average/neutral. For $100 dolars average rate/night I do expect decent treatment, decent conditions as listed above, and more!!!There isnt a coffee maker in the room, excuse me!? Subjective I know, but it's just terrible to not enjoy a slow start with a cup of coffee in bed! The choices are: to pay about 5.50 (small pot of coffee) + 5 (operation fee to all room service orders) + tax + gratuity = which comes to about what? 15 bucks coffee? or to face the world with your morning face, take the elevator to the starbucks &quot;conveniently located&quot; :D right outside the elevators, and get back in bed? Ridiculous! On the down side also, the rooms have outdated looking ac units, settings not very clear, difficult to adjust the room temperature in the winter; first night I woke up frozen, second night was okay but the unit started to make a loud noise that woke me up so I stopped it, third night just folded the blankets in two - that was a good nite, fourth night forgot the heater on -that never stopped and I ended up sick because of the overdry and heated air. Those with allergies/sinuses problems Beware! I ate once at the cafe-(dont remember the name Carson?), food was good. Room service was also good - the prices too - 6 dollars a mimosa:) The pastries at starbucks in the hotel were very fresh and delicious, especially the fruit tart, also cheesecake and danishes. I liked the New Years atmosphere on Fremont outside the hotel. I cannot comment on any other features of the hotel, as I only used it to sleep/rest, then went out sightseeing strip, hoover dam, etc.It's 8.50 + tips the shuttle to and from the airport, which I find convenient. It's about 5 dollars the bus to the strip from what I heard but havent used it. It' s 23 dollars the taxi from the strip -(Luxor area)back to the hotel. Note that it's almost impossible to find a taxi on a holiday night like New Year's Eve, we waited over 15 minutes for one -out of many passing by -to stop and then they ask &quot;how much are u willing to pay!?&quot; It's up to anyone's negociations skills and no less than double:) In conclusion, I would stay at GN again, but I will bring with me a coffee maker and a humidifier..of course, after I check out its competion on the strip first:)	
