Dec 27 2008 	My favorite property in Las Vegas!	I’m a Las Vegas local but I love to stay at hotels here in town when I see a good deal or have a birthday/anniversary. From the first time I visited the Golden Nugget I fell in love-the pool is amazing, the property maintains a touch of “old” but mostly new and updated, and a great location (I love Fremont). The property in my book gets an 11 out of 10 – the rooms are really nice at affordable rates (please tell me where you can find a 4 diamond resort in this country for $59 a night other then Las Vegas!?!), the amenities are amazing, and the Food &amp; Beverage outlets are impressive (although I would expect so much with the hotel now being run by a Food &amp; Beverage company). On this specific trip I stayed 2 nights for my birthday to pretty much drink at the pool during the day and relax in a nice comfy bed. We ate at the buffet for breakfast (2 for 1-$10) for a great breakfast buffet; we had room service-decent, and ate dinner one night at Grotto (very good we had a FEAST for $100 including a few drinks). My only complaint with the property was some of the customer service I received. I presently work for a strip property in customer service and have reasonable expectations (I understand things that might upset your typical guests and I try not to ask for too much BUT at the same time it takes an extra step to WOW me). The front desk clerk at check in wasn’t friendly and seemed to be just “doing his job” as we say – he didn’t explain anything to me I had to ask questions to get anything out of him. I had issues with the authorization on my card (they over authorized on incidentals) and when I called the front desk to ask why, I stated the clerk who checked me in told me it would only be $100 a night and I’m being hit $130 a night – they replied “the system sometimes does that”. I was using a debit that a family member had pre-paid for my trip for me as a gift with the exact amount for room &amp; tax + $100 incidentals on it. An authorization on a debit card is as good as a cash withdrawal in most circumstances – and asked the hotel manager that if my account over withdrew due to this lack of information given to me were they going to cover my over withdrawal fees passed on to my family member-they said no and were very rude about the situation. I clearly signed off on $100 incidentals a night on my registration card, so if I wanted to take legal action I could. Luckily no over withdrawal fees were passed and all was fine &amp; dandy with me-but it was the manner both front desk reps and managers handled the situation that left a sour taste in my mouth. On a positive note every dealer, server, and food &amp; beverage representative was great – I would highly suggest a retraining of the front desk staff on 4 Diamond Standards. The incident with the front desk will not keep me away from the G-Nug, I love it way too much, but some less understanding guests may not return if they were to encounter a similar incident.	
