Dec 2 2008 	Great Experience	My family and I and a few close friends just got back from Vegas over the Thanksgiving holiday. I am happy and pleased to say that my family and I were thrilled that we chose the Golden Nugget. Everything was just perfect from the time we arrived on Thursday, to the time we left on Monday. We absolutely have no complaints. We stayed in the North Tower and the rooms were nice. My friends who accompanied us chose to stay at the Venetian. Of course our room wasn't as luxurious, but guess where they kept wanting to go.... our hotel/downtown. While the strip is nice, downtown is sooo much more relaxed and not so stuffy. We ended up downtown every night until 3 in the morning. All the dealers we played with at the Nugget were very friendly. I learned to play blackjack this time and all the dealers were more than willing to help me learn and advise me how to play my hand. We did eat at the buffet one afternoon for lunch. As you check in, they give you a book of coupons that are valid at the hotel. One of the coupons is a buy one get one free buffet. The food wasn't bad. We both ate for 11.00 so I can't expect 5 star food. I will recommend the buffet at Rio. It has a wide variety of food. And the quality is good, however it is 25.00 a person. As everyone mentions, the pool area at the hotel is very nice. The pool is heated so there are a few people who swim during the day. They have a few blackjack tables out at the pool, so we hung out there one night. It was really nice because you could hear the sound of the water, they had heat lamps to keep you warm and you got to breathe a little fresh air. All in all, we enjoyed the Golden Nugget. This was our 3rd visit to Vegas and have always stayed on the strip. I can say from now on, we will definitely be staying at the Golden Nugget. Its a nice hotel for a great price.	
