Nov 24 2008 	Not So Golden	I booked a special &quot;VIP&quot; room at the Golden Nugget expecting something exceptional as this hotel is rated 4 stars. I was disappointed from the moment we got there. I stood in a long check-in line with only two staff members working behind the desk. After a long wait I discovered that I could have used their special VIP check-in area. They did not make this clear when I made my reservation. Access to our floor required that our key be put into a slot in the elevator. This made us feel special but the room did not live up to expectations. It was dark and had only one small window. The bathroom was small and the door opened so that it blocked the shower. The decor was above average for a hotel and the room had a big screen TV and a special bed which was very comfortable. For the extra price you got free bottled water, apples, and 4 bowls of candy in the hall by the elevators. We also got to use the spa for free which would otherwise have cost 20 dollars a day. The Golden Nugget is by far the nicest hotel downtown, but it does not come close to the nicer strip hotels many of which are also rated 4 stars. If you want to stay downtown, I would definitely recommend the Golden Nugget over any of the other hotels, but don't expect 4 star service or accomidations. I am not sure the VIP rooms are worth the extra price. The pool is not nearly as nice as it looks on the web site. It is relatively small and did not get much sun because it is surrounded on all sides by the hotel.	
